00:42.771 --> 00:44.628
{pub}You new in town?

00:44.794 --> 00:46.578
Yeah.

00:52.955 --> 00:55.055
You lookin' for work?

00:57.498 --> 01:02.270
I'm lookin' to do a job on the rail road.

01:07.351 --> 01:09.569
We'll ride in ones and twos,

01:10.027 --> 01:11.232
Morgan here, Burtee here,

01:11.357 --> 01:14.449
you got the sawmill, you watch
the saloon and the whorehouse.

01:17.303 --> 01:19.642
You wanna have another go?

01:33.176 --> 01:35.762
And, Dennis,
you take care of the boxcar guard.

01:35.928 --> 01:37.372
Jimmy, you watch from the restaurant.

01:37.397 --> 01:40.517
Me, Fitz, and Louie, we'll take the office.

01:50.182 --> 01:51.358
Ma'am.

01:51.483 --> 01:52.951
Ma'am.

01:59.493 --> 02:02.706
Just a blonde girl and a pencil
dick with 50,000 in the safe.

02:02.872 --> 02:04.749
When them Yankee bastards is out,

02:04.874 --> 02:06.419
we slip in and take their payroll.

02:06.544 --> 02:08.919
Easier'n butter's greasy, boys.

02:09.086 --> 02:10.797
The one guard all we got to worry about?

02:10.963 --> 02:14.551
You remember that nigger guard
on the train with the gun?

02:14.717 --> 02:16.219
The one that buffaloed Bohannon?

02:21.515 --> 02:24.377
Strutting around like
a big old black rooster.

02:24.502 --> 02:27.397
I knew somethin' weren't
right with him and Bohannon.

02:27.563 --> 02:32.611
And get this, Bohannon himself
is working on the rail road.

02:32.777 --> 02:34.237
Druther not run into no Bohannon.

02:34.403 --> 02:37.074
Shit, I ain't worried.

02:37.240 --> 02:39.868
Besides, he'll be miles away

02:40.034 --> 02:41.912
when we take that 50,000.

02:42.078 --> 02:43.080
Cullen's alive?

02:45.196 --> 02:47.959
Y'all secure them brakes this time.

02:50.962 --> 02:55.375
He's walkin' the streets
like the risen Christ.

03:24.578 --> 03:27.874
